Privacy Policy for ev-shops

Introduction
This Privacy Policy explains how ev-shops ("we", "us", or "our") collects, uses, and protects your personal information while utilizing the Bing Maps API for educational purposes. Our project is hosted on GitHub and is intended solely for non-commercial, educational use. We are committed to ensuring your privacy and handling your personal information responsibly.

1. Purpose of Data Collection
Our project uses the Bing Maps API to provide location-based features and functionalities for educational purposes. We specifically collect location data from users to enhance the projectâ€™s functionality, improve user experience, and demonstrate the capabilities of the Bing Maps API.

2. Information We Collect
When using our project, we may request the following information:

Geolocation Data: Your device's geographical location, which is collected only when you grant permission. This data is essential for the functioning of certain features in our project.
3. Use of Information
The location data collected will be used for the following purposes:

To Enable Project Functionality: To provide relevant location-based services within the project.
To Enhance Educational Value: To demonstrate how geolocation data can be utilized within applications powered by the Bing Maps API.
4. Data Retention
We do not store your personal data. The location data is used in real-time to facilitate the functionality of the project and is not retained after the session ends.

5. Sharing of Information
We do not share, sell, or disclose any personal information to third parties. The data you provide is used solely for the functionality of our project and is not stored or utilized beyond that purpose.

6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies
Our project does not use cookies or any tracking technologies to collect personal data. Check out Bing Maps API cookie policy. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.

7. Third-Party Links
Our project may contain links to external websites or resources. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites and encourage you to review their privacy policies.

8. Children's Privacy
This project is not intended for children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If we learn that we have collected such data, we will take steps to delete it.

9. Images
Utilized images from Pixabay and Pexels solely for educational purposes, ensuring compliance with their respective licensing agreements.

10. Compliance with Bing Maps Terms
We are committed to complying with the Bing Maps API's terms of service. This project is intended for educational use only, and we acknowledge that the project is powered by the Bing Maps API, as mentioned in the README file.

11. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected in this document, and we encourage you to review it periodically.

11. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our practices regarding your personal information, please refer to the Bing Maps API documentation for assistance..
